      <h1 class='title'>PROTECTION OF THE SUEZ CANAL</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='house-of-lords-report' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'> Deb 25 April 1951 vol 171 c498</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_498' title='Col. 498 &mdash;  Deb 25 April 1951 vol 171 c498' name='column_498' href='#column_498' rel='bookmark'>498</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0171P0-01442'>
        <a name='S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_11'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-robert-vansittart' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_11' title='Link to this speech by Mr Robert Vansittart' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-robert-vansittart" title="Mr Robert Vansittart">LORD VANSITTART</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            My Lords, I beg to ask the Question which stands in my name on the Order Paper.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0171P0-01443'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_12' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        [The Question was as follows:
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0171P0-01444'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_13' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        To ask His Majesty's Government whether Parliament will be consulted before any irreparable risk is run in regard to the protection of the Suez Canal.]
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0171P0-01445'>
        <a name='S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_14'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-william-henderson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_14' title='Link to this speech by Mr William Henderson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-william-henderson" title="Mr William Henderson">THE PARLIAMENTARY UNDER-SECRETARY OF STATE FOR FOREIGN AFFAIRS (LORD HENDERSON)</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            My Lords. I think my right honourable friend the Foreign Secretary has recently made it clear, in a statement which he made in another place on April 11, that while His Majesty's Government's treaty-making power must be preserved in this, as in other cases, Parliament will have an opportunity to confirm or reject any agreement reached with the Egyptian Government on this matter before it enters into force. I have nothing to add to this statement, except to repeat that both His Majesty's Government and the Egyptian Government have agreed that neither of them should comment at present on the matters under discussion between themselves.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0171P0-01446'>
        <a name='S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_15'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-robert-vansittart' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0171P0_19510425_HOLR2_15' title='Link to this speech by Mr Robert Vansittart' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-robert-vansittart" title="Mr Robert Vansittart">LORD VANSITTART</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            My Lords, I thank the noble Lord for his statement which does not, however, entirely remove my apprehensions. I will take an opportunity of trying to explain them in more detail next week.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
